SUMMARY:Seed Starting Tips and Techniques
DTSTAMP:20260318T234503Z
DTSTART:20260328T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Taught by Nancy Kartes and Bill Thorness. Our mild late winter 
	allows us to sprout the edible garden early. Getting growing now will mean
	 longer harvests and more use of our garden throughout the year. Learn wha
	t can be started now\, whether to choose seeds or starts\, where to site y
	our early spring garden\, how to know when the soil is ready\, and how to 
	plan ahead for the best success. Hands-on lessons will also teach you how 
	to make a “seed snail\,” how to use a soil block\, and how to make your ow
	n seed-starting mix! You’ll also go home with some early-season seeds read
	y to sprout. $24.50 BBGS Member/$35 Non-Member.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcit
	y.com/events/#/details/seed-starting-tips-and-techniques/17923225/2026-03-
	28T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/seed-starting-tips-and-te
	chniques/17923225/2026-03-28T00
LOCATION:Bellevue Botanical Garden\, 12001 Main St\, Bellevue\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
